by kayla howey
sharing inspired recipes for your kitchen table
all recipes linked below!✨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on August 16, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: there’s nothing like a sweet & savory marinated stone fruit “caprese” salad to celebrate summer! the fruit is tossed with red wine vinegar, honey, olive oil, and plenty of herbs. after a quick marinade, it’s all spooned over creamy buffalo mozzarella cheese. you can serve it with toasted bread or just eat it as is! recipe linked in my bio!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on August 13, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: weekend plans: making this plum galette! it’s got a golden, flaky crust with a sweet & juicy plum filling. the whole process of making it - rolling out the dough, arranging the plums, folding the edges, drizzling on the brown sugar syrup, baking until bubbling, scooping the ice cream to melt over top - is so relaxing! the perfect weekend baking project. best part is you can use any stone fruit for this, so throw in what you’ve got! recipe linked in my bio!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on August 12, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: grilled pepper potato salad with creamy mustard dressing…a fun twist on the classic summer side dish. full of sweet & spicy peppers, crispy potatoes, hard-boiled eggs, green onions & radishes, and lots of fresh herbs. recipe linked in my bio!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on August 11, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: the SIMPLEST cherry tomato pasta with creamy burrata cheese. if you ever have a bunch of tomatoes & need an easy weeknight dinner…this is it. recipe linked in my bio!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on August 06, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: balsamic marinated skirt steak…grilled until tender and sliced thin, topped with a sweet & spicy red pepper relish, and served with a raw shaved zucchini salad that’s got lemon and herbs and a mound of parmesan cheese over top. serve this with some pasta on the side (maybe my creamy corn fettuccine) for the perfect weekend summer meal! recipe linked in my bio!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on August 02, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, food and indoor.

node.text: quintessential summer recipes continue with my busia’s sour cream cucumbers! cooling & refreshing, the perfect counterpart to something hot off the grill. they’ve got a nice onion bite from scallions and chives, plus lots of black pepper. beyond simple & incredibly tasty. such a great addition to any meal. recipe linked in my bio!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on July 30, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: prosciutto & melon! sweet cantaloupe topped with salty prosciutto, balsamic soaked shallots, toasted pine nuts, lemon, parmesan, and basil. it’s my version of the classic sweet & savory italian dish…and it is simply the perfect combination of flavors. recipe linked in my bio!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on July 29, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: an easy zucchini pasta with lots of fresh summer zucchini, lemon, parmesan, a little butter & a splash of cream. topped with creamy ricotta cheese & fresh basil. it’s a quick-cooking pasta that you can make all summer long. serve it as a side or make a big bowl of this as your main meal. there’s nothing not to love in here! recipe linked in my bio!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on July 28, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: you can’t do summer without this heirloom tomato gazpacho! it’s the most vibrant, refreshing summer soup that’s creamy, tangy, and full of bright flavor. such an easy recipe that highlights summer produce at its best. serve it with grilled bread for dipping to make it even better. perfect way to start any meal. recipe linked in my bio!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Original Dish on July 27, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: green goddess salmon with peach salad! a fresh, healthy, and absolutely delicious summer dinner you can make any night of the week. simply seared salmon topped with a tangy, herby green goddess yogurt sauce and served with a sweet and refreshing salad alongside. all you need to do is add on some potatoes or rice & you’re good to go! recipe linked in my bio!!
